remarks.format:
## Remarks
`SKFourByteTag` wraps a 32-bit value whose four bytes are interpreted as ASCII characters. Four-byte tags are used throughout OpenType to identify font tables (e.g. `'c','m','a','p'`), variation axes (e.g. `'w','g','h','t'` for weight), and other named features.
Create a tag from four characters using the `(char, char, char, char)` constructor, or from a string with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFourByteTag.Parse(System.String)>. The string overload pads to four characters with spaces if the input is shorter.
Implicit conversions to and from `uint` are provided for interoperability.
This type is a value type and does not require disposal.
## Examples
```csharp // Create the weight variation axis tag 'wght' var wght = new SKFourByteTag('w', 'g', 'h', 't');
// Or parse from a string var wghtParsed = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght");
Console.WriteLine(wght == wghtParsed); // True Console.WriteLine(wght.ToString()); // "wght" ```
